<F P=100> SLOVAKIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Signed Contract Meets Indian Army Requirements </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2603182194 Prague HOSPODARSKE NOVINY in Czech 23 Mar 94 p 4 </F>
<F P=103> AU2603182194 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague HOSPODARSKE NOVINY </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Czech </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [CTK report: "A Contract With India"] </F>
  [Text] Kosice--The director of the East Slovak Engineering 
Works [VSS], I. Dufinec, has signed a memorandum with the Indian 
BEML company on cooperation in commencing special production for 
the requirements of the Indian Army and for joint commercial 
purposes in specific territories. This involves the type-AV 15 
military tow trucks that the VSS is assembling on Tatra 
undercarriages. A similar contract with a partner in the United 
Arab Emirates should be signed this year, and negotiations are 
under way with Syria, among other countries. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

