<F P=100> SLOVAKIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Privatization Inquiry Halts Property Transfers </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2603181994 Bratislava PRAVDA in Slovak 23 Mar 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> AU2603181994 </F>
<F P=104>  Bratislava PRAVDA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Slovak </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [TA SR report: "Transfers Frozen"] </F>
  [Text] Bratislava--Rudolf Filkus, minister of finance of 
the Slovak Republic, has temporarily frozen transfers of 
National Property Fund securities in the Securities Center 
[SCP]. As Dusan Koledzaj, director of the Slovak Finance 
Ministry's Capital Market Department, informed TA SR yesterday, 
this temporary measure went into effect as of 18 March 1994. 
The minister had been asked to take this step by Milan 
Janicina, minister for the administration and privatization of 
national property, on the basis of a preliminary inquiry into 
privatization projects approved by the previous government of 
Vladimir Meciar after 15 February, until the ministry's analysis 
is wound up. 
  [Bratislava PRAVDA in Slovak on 24 March on page 2 carries a 
250-word TA SR report entitled "Inquiry Into Privatization." 
The report quotes Milan Janicina, minister for the 
administration and privatization of national property, as having 
told a news conference on 23 March that Prime Minister Meciar's 
government "approved approximately 45 privatization projects 
after 15 February, of which an estimated third do not conform to 
existing legislation." Janicina also said that those 
privatization projects that are "in conformity with the law and 
morality" will be respected.] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

