<H3> <TI>   Addresses SDA Meeting </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2603222994 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 2100 GMT 26 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2603222994 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Alija Izetbegovic, president of the 
Bosnia-Herzegovina Presidency, addressed today's session of the 
main committee of the Party of Democratic Action [SDA] with the 
following words: 
  In our assessment we should prevent the continuation of a 
war 
waged on two fronts, which is suffocating us. We have reached 
the conclusion that one front has to be extinguished, and that 
it would be better and less painful if it were done with the 
Croats. True, our wounds are still fresh from the conflict with 
them, but they are nonetheless lighter than the ones inflicted 
on us by the Serbs. 
  It is also important to say that the chetniks' loathsome 
project had the support of their academicians and the church, 
which is not the case with the Croatian policy. The Croats did 
not have the backing of either the church or of a large number 
of people in Croatia. Fewer people in Croatia have messed 
things up, Izetbegovic said. 

</TEXT>

