<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Bosnian Croats Approve Federation Constitution </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2603200094 Zagreb HTV Television in Serbo-Croatian 1830 
GMT 26 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2603200094 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb HTV Television </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] We begin the news with a report from the session 
of the chamber of deputies of the Croat republic of 
Herceg-Bosna, held in Mostar: 
  Today, in a warm and quiet Mostar, the Chamber of Deputies 
of 
the Croat republic of Herceg-Bosna approved the constitution of 
the federation of Bosnia-Herzegovina and tasked the Croat 
deputies -- members of the constituent assembly [of 
Bosnia-Herzegovina] -- with approving the constitution at the 
Bosnia-Herzegovina Assembly session in Sarajevo on 28 March. 
[passage omitted] 
  Following the opening speeches, the discussions were held 
behind closed doors. A committee for monitoring the discussion 
this evening proposed the following conclusions: To form a 
delegation of the Croat republic of Herceg-Bosna, comprising 
Kresimir Zubak, Jadranko Prlic and General Ante Roso, which will 
attend the work of the constitutent assembly in Sarajevo on 
Monday, in addition to the deputies. A body for conducting 
political talks with the Muslim side on all issues is also to be 
formed, and will include Kresimir Zubak, Ivo Zivkovic, Perica 
Jukic, and Ivica Lucic. 
  In addition to these items, the agenda of the Chamber of 
Deputies includes several draft laws. Discussion is under way. 

</TEXT>

