<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Bosnian, Croat Commanders Sign Agreement </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2603163194 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1400 GMT 26 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2603163194 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Army General Rasim Delic, chief of general staff of 
the Bosnia-Herzegovina Army, and Colonel General Ante Roso, 
chief of general staff of the Croat Defense Council [HVO], 
signed an agreement in Sarajevo today on the organization of the 
joint command of the Bosnia-Herzegovina Army and the HVO. The 
agreement defines the organization and tasks of the joint 
commands in the interim period, the Bosnia-Herzegovina Army 
press center reports. It was agreed that joint commands in 
sectors and military districts should become operational as soon 
as possible. According to the agreement the organization of the 
federal army, i.e., the army of the federation, will follow 
immediately after the proclamation of the federal constitution. 

</TEXT>

