<H3> <TI>   Serbs Reportedly Attack Tesanj Hospital </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2803150494 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1303 GMT 28 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2803150494 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Mirudin Aldobasic from Tesanj] </F>
  [Text] From their well-known strongholds, the chetniks 
launched several hundred shells at the Tesanj field hospital. 
Schools and other civilian buildings in Tesanj were also shelled 
one after another. We have as yet no information on the 
casualties. 
  In the Tesanj area, and in the area of the free territories 
of Doboj and Teslic, the population is in shelters. The joint 
units of the 7 South Operative Group are decisively and 
courageously defending their positions. The villages of the 
free territories in this area, particularly Grlic, Planje, 
Kalosevic, Mijonac, and Krakov, are [words indistinct]. 
Therefore, the aggressor is not giving up on his criminal 
intentions aimed at capturing these free territories, 
particularly the Doboj-Teslic road communication. 

</TEXT>

