  [Excerpt] Ferocious fighting is in progress along the 
Tesanj-Teslic front lines and in a wide area around Crni Vrh. 
Joint units of the Seven-South operational zone are liberating 
the hitherto occupied territories of the Teslic municipality and 
linking up with the units of the Bosnia-Herzegovina Army's 3d 
Corps in a triumphant operation. Hajrudin Reidzovic reports: 
  At the time of this report strategic front lines were pushed 
forward by the capture of a piece of territory 6 km long and 
1.5-2 km deep. Important facilities [objekti], which have 
served as the most important strongholds of the Serb aggressors 
since the beginning of the war, have been captured: Kuzno 
Groblje PT 675, Vis Plane PT 677, hill 655, Tresnjev Panj and 
[name indistinct], name] or hill 497. [sentence as heard] Husar 
and Omerovo Guvno, notorious chetnik strongholds for the past 22 
months, from which they have killed civilians, especially 
children, are also about to fall. 
  At this moment our units are advancing relentlessly toward 
the south and the southwest. This is the collapse of the 
strategy of war criminal General Mladic. The number of dead 
aggressor soldiers exceeds 50, and twice as many have been 
injured and thus taken out of action. A substantial amount of 
arms and ammunition and military equipment has been seized. 
[passage omitted] 

