<H3> <TI>   Convention of Sarajevo Serbs Concludes </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2703191494 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1800 GMT 27 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2703191494 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] A convention of citizens of Serb nationality 
ended in Sarajevo today with the adoption of a declaration 
expressing the firm will of the Serb people living in the free 
part of Bosnia-Herzegovina to live in peace in a single 
Bosnia-Herzegovina within its internationally recognized 
borders. [passage omitted] 
  In its declaration, the convention stresses that no 
political 
goals can justify the suffering of innocent population, genocide 
and ethnic cleansing, particularly suffered by the Bosniak 
people. It stresses that the future of Bosnia-Herzegovina lies 
in its independence and sovereignty within the internationally 
recognized borders. Both the declaration and the proclamation 
on the convocation of a convention of trust energetically urge 
the strictest punishment by the international tribunal of all 
war criminals. The convocation of the convention of trust 
itself is necessary because interethnic trust will not be 
restored easily and quickly, while the convention can contribute 
to this hard and painstaking process. [passage omitted] 
  Let us just add in conclusion that the convention of the 
citizens of Serb nationality ended with the election of the Serb 
Civic Forum [Srpski gradjanski forum]. Mirko Pejanovic was 
elected president of the 32-member forum. 

</TEXT>

