<F P=100> SLOVAKIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Defense Minister, Others Installed </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2603182494 Bratislava PRAVDA in Slovak 23 Mar 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> AU2603182494 </F>
<F P=104>  Bratislava PRAVDA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Slovak </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [TA SR report: "Improving the Quality of the Army's Work"] </F>
  [Text] Bratislava--Slovak Prime Minister Jozef Moravcik 
installed new Defense Minister Pavol Kanis in his post yesterday 
at a meeting with Defense Ministry military and civilian 
personnel. Major General Andrej Sabol was appointed Defense 
Ministry state secretary and Colonel Rudolf Zidek was appointed 
head of the Defense Ministry Office. In his speech, the prime 
minister emphasized that the Slovak Republic requires 
high-quality and advanced Army and patriotic soldiers, who will 
fulfill their tasks regardless of which political grouping is in 
power. In expressing his appreciation, Minister Kanis said, 
among other things, that, in the coming weeks, it will be 
necessary to prepare a thorough analysis of the Slovak Army's 
first year. It is essential to improve the style and method of 
managerial work at the Defense Ministry and the Slovak Army 
Command "because the current system in many ways still resembles 
the old bipolar system," emphasized Kanis. 

</TEXT>

