<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Adopts Federation Constitution </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2703173194 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1700 GMT 27 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2703173194 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] At its session today, presided over by Dr. Haris 
Silajdzic, the government adopted the report by the delegation 
of the Republic of Bosnia-Herzegovina on the negotiations and 
the signing of the Washington agreement. 
  The government examined and adopted the draft Constitution 
of 
the Federation of Bosnia-Herzegovina as well as the drafts of 
other documents stemming from the Washington agreement. The 
government decided to recommend the adoption of the document to 
the Bosnia-Herzegovina Assembly. 
  At its session today the government also examined the draft 
of a preliminary agreement between the U.S. Government and the 
Republic of Bosnia-Herzegovina on economic, technical, and other 
forms of assistance. 

</TEXT>

