<F P=100> CROATIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Tudjman Ousts Manolic From Posts in HDZ </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2503180294 Zagreb VJESNIK in Serbo-Croatian 25 Mar 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> AU2503180294 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb VJESNIK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [HINA report: "Josip Manolic Removed as Member of the </F>
Croatian Democratic Community Presidency and member of the 
Central Committee of the Croatian Democratic Community"] 
  [Text] Zagreb -- On the basis of Article 2, Paragraph 33, 
and in accordance with Article 3, Paragraph 11 of the Croatian 
Democratic Community [HDZ] Statute, and on the recommendation of 
the HDZ Presidency and Main Secretariat, HDZ President Franjo 
Tudjman passed a decision stripping Mr. Josip Manolic of his 
duties as a member of the HDZ Presidency and a member of the HDZ 
Central Committee because of his repeated public disagreement 
with the policy of the HDZ as expressed in Croatian state 
policy, which contributed to the strengthening of Croatia's 
international position and internal democratic organization. 
This decision is also a request for the initiation of legal 
proceedings before the appropriate court of honor. The decision 
is effective immediately. This statement was issued by the HDZ 
on Thursday [24 Mar] afternoon. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

