<H3> <TI>   Decree Lists 24 Persons Pardoned </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2603191594 Bucharest Radio Romania Network in Romanian 
2000 GMT 25 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2603191594 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest Radio Romania Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Romanian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] According to constitutional stipulations, the 
Romanian president has signed a decree on the basis of which the 
penalties applied to the following convicts are pardoned: 
Gheorghe Dorus, Ion Manole, and Gabriela Cristina Muresan. 
  Pardoned from the execution of the rest of their penalties 
are the convicts Stefan Andrei, Silviu Curticeanu, Suzanica 
Gadea, Mihai Gere, Dan Ludlin, Ana Muresan, Eva Eugenia Nicolau, 
Titu Popescu, Constantin Radu, Ion Stoian, and Ion Toma. 
  One-third of the penalties applied to the following convicts 
are pardoned: (Veronica Gansmer) and Ioan Popa. 
  Two-thirds of the penalties applied to the following 
convicts 
are pardoned: Pavel Ambrus and Istvan Nagy. 
  Three-quarters of the penalties applied to the following 
convicts are pardoned: Mihaly Balint, Ferenc Boldizsar, Istvan 
Illyes, Laszlo Karsai, Imre Nagy, and Elod Vas Kiss. 
  The decree is dated 24 March 1994. 

</TEXT>

