<H3> <TI>   Delegation Leader Comments on Sarajevo Talks </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2803134294 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in Serbo-Croatian 
1300 GMT 28 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2803134294 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb Radio Croatia Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] The Croat delegation to the Sarajevo talks 
numbers 44 members in all, 28 of whom are deputies in the 
assembly of Herceg-Bosna. They are being led by Kresimir Zubak, 
president of the Presidential Council of the Croat republic of 
Herceg-Bosna, Ivan Bender, president of the Chamber of Deputies, 
Prime Minister Jadranko Prlic, and General Ante Roso. 
  Prior to their departure, Kresimir Zubak told us: 
  [Begin Zubak recording] I am convinced that we will reach 
agreement in Sarajevo regarding the procedures of the session 
itself and that we will this evening in Sarajevo also approve 
the draft [constitution]. 
  It is envisaged that when the constitution comes into 
effect, 
if it is approved this evening, then it should come into effect 
tonight at 2400. The next day there should be elections for the 
interim president and vice president of the federation, but 
these elections must be preceded by a political agreement. [end 
recording] [passage omitted] 

