<H3> <TI>   Tudjman Apologizes to Jewish Community </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2803183694 Zagreb HTV Television in Serbo-Croatian 1730 
GMT 28 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2803183694 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb HTV Television </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] Croatian President Franjo Tudjman this evening 
received a film personality of world acclaim -- Branko Lustig, 
the producer of "Schindler's List" -- and awarded him with the 
Order of Prince Trpimir. [passage omitted] 
  Tudjman said: As president of today's democratic state of 
Croatia, I take this opportunity to apologize to you and all 
members of the Jewish community on behalf of those who took part 
in the Holocaust and enforced the Nazi-fascist racist laws in 
the NDH [the Independent State of Croatia, a World War II Nazi 
puppet-state]. At the same time, it is with pleasure that I 
stress the historical truth that the large majority of the 
Croatian nation condemned all types of that criminal policy, and 
many Croats took an active part in the antifascist struggle, 
including myself, who, as a young man fought for four years. It 
is probably not a coincidence that it is a man like myself -- a 
man from the ranks of the Croatian antifascist movement -- who 
is leading the modern democratic Croatian state, but neither is 
the fact that your hometown Osijek came under threat in our 
time, and its surroundings suffered the crime of ethnic 
cleansing. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

