Serbo-Croatian 1443 GMT 28 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2803152794 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Belgrade, 28 Mar (TANJUG) -- Yugoslav Foreign 
Minister Vladislav Jovanovic today received 'Ali 'Abd-al-Salam 
al-Turyaki, special envoy of the head of state of the Great 
Socialist People's Libyan Arab Jamahiriyah. 
  In the course of the meeting, which passed in a friendly 
atmosphere, the two sides discussed latest developments on the 
territory of the former Socialist Federal Republic of 
Yugoslavia, the situation in the former Yugoslav republic of 
Bosnia-Herzegovina, and perspectives for bilateral 
Yugoslav-Jamahiriyah cooperation, the Federal Ministry of 
Foreign Affairs has announced. 

