<H3> <TI>   Libyan Special Envoy Makes Official Visit </TI></H3>
<H4>   Meets With Minister Unkovic </H4>
<F P=102> LD2903111994 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1037 GMT 29 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2903111994 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Belgrade, 29 Mar (TANJUG)-- Dr. Milorad Unkovic, the 
federal minister for foreign economic relations, today received 
Dr. 'Ali 'Abd al-Salam al-Turyaki, the special envoy of Libyan 
leader Col. Mu'ammar al-Qadhdhafi. 
  It has been announced that the cordial and friendly talks 
confirmed the hitherto good bilateral relations between the 
Federal Republic of Yugoslavia and Libya. Minister Unkovic 
stressed his satisfaction at the fact that, even in the 
conditions of sanctions under which the two countries are 
living, there is an interest and desire for the best possible 
level of cooperation. 
  Trade between the two countries prior to the introduction of 
sanctions by the international community was exceptionally 
important to Yugoslavia so that efforts to revitalize 
cooperation in future are an exceptional pleasure. 
  Envoy al-Turyaki expressed Libya's readiness to send 
humanitarian aid to Yugoslavia via the Red Cross. According to 
him, this is only a small symbol by which Libya wishes to show 
its goodwill and understanding for its old Yugoslav friends. 

