<F P=101> Kosovo </F>
<H3> <TI>   Serbian Police Confiscate Reporters' Notes </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2403185294 Tirana TVSH Television Network in Albanian 1735 
GMT 24 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2403185294 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana TVSH Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Albanian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] At about 1500 today, Serbian police intervened in 
the Kosova Information Center [QIK] offices in Prishtina. The 
offices are situated in the Qafa complex of business buildings 
in Prishtina. Today, they were held under the continuous 
supervision of the Serbian police. 
  Serbian civilians, who first entered the QIK offices, played 
the role of uninformed citizens. Then, at about 1500, two 
plainclothes policemen entered the offices and took personal 
notes from three QIK reporters. 
  At 1510, four policemen entered the offices. Two of the 
policemen were holding automatic weapons. They ordered the 
reporters to stop work. Meanwhile, the Serbian policemen 
confiscated personal notes from seven QIK reporters. 
  The QIK reports that the Serbian police showed interest in 
the work performed at the office and left, taking the notes with 
them. 

</TEXT>

