<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Croats Refuse To Enter Sarajevo Assembly Hall </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2903125494 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1201 GMT 29 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2903125494 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Belgrade, 29 Mar (TANJUG) -- The radio of the Croat 
republic of Herceg-Bosna has reported that this morning Croat 
deputies refused to enter the hall in Sarajevo, where the 
Muslim-Croat assembly is meeting, until Croat national symbols 
are displayed along with Muslim symbols. 
  Ivan Bender, chairman of the chamber of deputies of the 
Assembly of the Croat republic of Herceg-Bosna, told Croatian TV 
upon his arrival in Sarajevo that he would lodge a protest 
against the decision to start the Assembly proceedings without 
delegates from the Croatian Democratic Union of former 
Bosnia-Herzegovina. According to Muslim Sarajevo radio, today's 
session has been postponed and will start at 1400. 

</TEXT>

