<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Constitution To Be Approved </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2903133394 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in Serbo-Croatian 
1300 GMT 29 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2903133394 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb Radio Croatia Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The constituent assembly of Bosnia-Herzegovina, 
which is supposed to approve the constitution of the new state 
federation, will be held tomorrow morning. This was stated to 
HINA [Croatian news agency] by Ivan Bender, president of the 
Chamber of Deputies of the Croat republic of Herceg-Bosna. 
According to him, after the end of tomorrow's constituent 
assembly of Bosnia-Herzegovina, deputies of the Croat republic 
of Herceg-Bosna will leave Sarajevo in the afternoon. 
  Otherwise, the work of the regular assembly of 
Bosnia-Herzegovina is continuing. The debate is about the draft 
constitution and the Washington agreement. The resumption of 
this session was planned for 1400 but up until this broadcast 
went on air, HINA's correspondent in Sarajevo had not obtained 
confirmation of this. 

</TEXT>

