<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Bihac Deputies Support Federation Constitution </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2803223594 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 2200 GMT 28 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2803223594 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Deputies of the Bihac assembly discussed the 
draft constitution of the Bosnia-Herzegovina federation at a 
session today. After an introductory speech by Mirsad Delagic, 
Bosnian government minister for regional coordination for the 
Bihac-Banja Luka district, and statements by the republic's 
deputies Adem Ibrahimpasic and Ejub Topic, deputies of the Bihac 
assembly praised this historic document and fully approved the 
proposed constitution. They also concluded that -- due to 
administrative mistakes -- a protest must be lodged with the 
chairman and the secretary general of the Bosnia-Herzegovina 
parliament to request that invitations and documents for future 
sessions be sent to the Bihac deputies. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

