<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Krajisnik Alleges UNPROFOR Bias </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2803155294 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1505 GMT 28 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2803155294 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Novi Sad, 28 Mar (TANJUG) -- Momcilo Krajisnik, 
speaker of the assembly of the Srpska republic, has described as 
strange the behavior and mediation of UN Protection Force 
members in most places where the Muslim spring offensive has 
begun. In a statement to Radio Novi Sad, he assessed that UN 
forces are attempting to calm the situation only in places where 
the Muslim forces are not having successes. "It is for precisely 
this reason that we have sent a protest to the United Nations, 
stressing in particular the examples of the battlefields near 
Maglaj, Bihac, and some others," Krajisnik added. He stressed 
that forecasts of a Muslim offensive have turned out to be true 
and he confirmed that Muslims are obtaining weapons from abroad. 

</TEXT>

