<H3> <TI>   LDS Leader on Jansa Removal </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2903082194 Ljubljana Radio Slovenia Network in Slovene 
0500 GMT 29 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2903082194 </F>
<F P=104>  Ljubljana Radio Slovenia Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Slovene </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The head of the club of deputies of the Liberal 
Democracy Party [LDS], Jozef Skoljc, says that the proposal to 
impeach minister Jansa was not a proposal to alter the political 
balance of powers: 
  [Begin Skoljc recording] In a way, at least in my opinion, 
it is very problematic if the cooperation in the coalition is 
made conditional on a certain minister being untouchable. This 
is a new position in these talks and neither the Christian 
Democrats nor the Social Democrats have ever championed this 
position so far. 
  It is also rather nonpolitical to say that the Social 
Democrats equal Janez Jansa. The Social Democrats were given an 
opportunity to take part in the government. Now, whether they 
will decide for cooperation or not is another matter. However, 
the fact is that whenever somebody has been replaced so far, 
parties did not leave the government coalition because of it. 
Woe to those parties that are prisoners of the ambitions of 
their presidents! [end recording] 

</TEXT>

