<H3> <TI>   Social Democrats Leave Coalition </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2903080894 Ljubljana Radio Slovenia Network in Slovene 
0500 GMT 29 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2903080894 </F>
<F P=104>  Ljubljana Radio Slovenia Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Slovene </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Joze Pucnik, head of the club of deputies of the 
Social Democrats, gave the following statement: 
  [Begin Pucnik recording] I shall say it directly -- the 
Social Democrats no longer have any business in this coalition. 
The manner in which the prime minister got rid of our 
president, the defense minister [Janez Jansa], is such that even 
discussion is no longer possible. What next? Regarding certain 
issues, we have been in opposition so far. Now we will, of 
course, pursue these things even more consistently. The 
opposition parties do not have much scope and the same applies 
to us. We will shift the focus of our activity outside the 
parliament, in strengthening the organization, attracting new 
members, and forming new local organizations, and thus, 
preparing ourselves for the local elections that will take place 
at the end of this year. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

