<F P=100> CZECH REPUBLIC </F>
<H3> <TI>   Klaus: Coalition Failed To Reach `Compromise' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2903121194 Prague Radiozurnal Radio Network in Czech 1000 
GMT 29 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2903121194 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague Radiozurnal Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Czech </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The political committee of the Civic Democratic 
Party met in Prague today. The party chairman, Vaclav Klaus, 
told Czech radio about the meeting: 
  [Begin Klaus recording] Today's meeting discussed the 
outcome 
of the talks of the Coalition Four held yesterday and confirmed, 
more or less, our basic positions. As far as election laws are 
concerned, we have still not managed to reach a compromise, or 
what could be termed its essence. We repeat that our current 
positions on this issue are still valid. These positions have 
been voiced on many occasions, and, as far as this case is 
concerned, they happen to be identical with those contained in 
the government's proposal, which is already in parliament. 
  To pursue any further talks in this respect, our party's 
political committee has authorized the chairman to negotiate 
possible compromises with the coalition partners. That is one 
thing. 
  As for the other topics, a consultation on the next course 
of 
action to be taken with regard to Jewish property is to take 
place later today. Several of our ministers will attend. I 
think these are the main matters we are currently interested in. 
[end recording] 

</TEXT>

