<H3> <TI>   Further Reportage on Dariusz Rosati Candidacy </TI></H3>
<H4>   Conservative Party on Rejection </H4>
<F P=102> LD2903121794 Warsaw Radio Warszawa Network in Polish 1005 
GMT 29 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2903121794 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw Radio Warszawa Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Polish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Aleksander Hall, chairman of the Conservative Party 
[PK], has expressed the view that the rejection of Dariusz 
Rosati's candidacy for the posts of deputy prime minister and 
minister of finance marks the beginning of Lech Walesa's 
presidential campaign. In an interview for Radio Zet, Hall 
described the recent events as another step undermining 
democracy. 

</TEXT>

