<F P=100> POLAND </F>
<H3> <TI>   Only UN Bans Apply in Trade With Burma </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2803221294 Warsaw Third Program Radio Network in Polish 
2100 GMT 28 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2803221294 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw Third Program Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Polish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The United States has announced that it will send a 
diplomatic note to Poland, asking that no assistance be given to 
the regime in Burma. The Americans maintain that the Poles are 
helping the local junta by providing military training and 
maintenance of military equipment. 
  Here is Wladyslaw Klaczynski, the director of the Foreign 
Affairs Ministry Information Department: 
  [Begin recording] [Klaczynski] So far, the Foreign Affairs 
Ministry has received nothing from the Americans. 
  We have not sold assault helicopters. Two years ago we sold 
transport helicopters from Swidnik. Allegedly, the Burmese have 
installed some weapons in them. This could happen. 
  I would like to recall that Burma is not subject to any ban 
by the United Nations Organization. 
  [Unidentified correspondent] Precisely, are we bound by UN 
bans or by U.S. bans? 
  [Klaczynski] We are bound only by UN bans and by our own 
morality. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

