<H3> <TI>   Csoti Welcomes European Stability Agreement </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2603172094 Budapest MTI in English 1325 GMT 25 Mar 94 -- 
FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU2603172094 </F>
<F P=104>  Budapest MTI </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Budapest, 25 March (MTI) -- Hungary welcomes the 
draft European Stability Agreement being outlined on the basis 
of the Balladur plan, the foreign affairs executive of the 
Hungarian Democratic Forum (MDF), Gyorgy Csoti, said at his 
press conference in Budapest on Friday [25 March]. The first 
conference on the agreement is expected to be held in May, based 
on the preparatory work. 
  Csoti said a condition for the successful conference is that 
representatives of the Hungarian national minorities living in 
the different countries be present at the talks. The politician 
said no decision can be reached about the minorities without 
them. 
  Csoti noted with regret that, contrary to the expectations, 
no positive changes have come about in Romania and the related 
recommendations of the Council of Europe were not fulfilled. 
  He said it is distressing that no commemorations were heard 
in Romanian legislature in Hungarian to mark March 15, the 
Hungarian national day, the anniversary of the outbreak of the 
1848-49 revolution and freedom fight. Csoti said the senior 
political forces in Bucharest rely on extreme nationalist, 
chauvinistic parties. 

</TEXT>

