<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Romania </F>
<H3> <TI>   Vacaroiu, Demirel Discuss Stability in Balkans </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2403194594 Bucharest ROMPRES in English 1803 GMT 24 Mar 94 
-- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU2403194594 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest ROMPRES </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bucharest, ROMPRES 24/3/1994 -- Both countries' wish 
to develop the traditional Romanian-Turkish relations was 
highlighted during the formal interview in Bucharest on 24 March 
between President Suleyman Demirel of Turkey and Romanian Prime 
Minister Nicolae Vacaroiu. 
  During the first minutes of the interview, when the press 
was 
allowed to attend, Premier Vacaroiu referred to the constant 
support Turkey has given Romania in this difficult period. He 
said the bilateral trade topped last year the 400 million dollar 
mark, which however did not reflect the two countries' real 
potential. The same was said by the Turkish president, who 
showed the trade ought to reach one billion dollars. 
  President Demirel also assessed that Romania and Turkey 
could 
help develop a multilateral cooperation in the Black Sea area 
and achieving stability in the Balkans. He also referred to the 
need to intensify the links between the two countries' 
businessmen, and their collaboration in third markets. 
  "It is up to us to open the way," he added. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

