<H3> <TI>   Serb `Torturing' of Albanian Officers Protested </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2603194394 Tirana ATA in English 1113 GMT 25 Mar 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU2603194394 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana ATA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tirana, March 25 (ATA) -- The Human Rights and 
Freedoms Defence Council in Prishtina protested on March 24 
against the torturing of three former Albanian officers Ismet 
Veliqi, Avdi Behrami, and Azem Gasgi who have been imprisoned in 
Mitrovica. The protest which was signed by the chairman of the 
council, Adem Demaci, pointed out that according to reports, the 
prisoners are subjected to barbarous tortures, such as electric 
batons, chemicals and other means. 
  The Journalists' Association of Kosova protested against the 
60 days imprisonment by the Serbian Court in Prishtina of the 
reporter Shaip Beqiri, who has served sentences by the Serbian 
prisons several times before. According to the association, the 
latest imprisonment is made in the course of punishments and 
persecutions of Albanian reporters and creators in Kosova by 
Serbian authorities. 

</TEXT>

