<F P=102>  AU2803102194 Prague CTK in English 2148 GMT 27 Mar 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU2803102194 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Presov, East Slovakia, March 27 (CTK) -- The 
Movement for a Democratic Slovakia (HZDS) today called on the 
present government coalition not to drive the critical situation 
to a head but stick to political culture. In a statement from a 
two-day HZDS conference which ended today, the HZDS urged the 
government to halt dismissals of state functionaries for 
political reasons. 
  HZDS Chairman Vladimir Meciar delivered a closing speech to 
the conference, but journalists were not briefed about its 
details. At a press conference earlier in the day, Meciar hinted 
his speech would analyze the situation in Slovakia since the 
June 1992 parliamentary election to date. He said that 
shortcomings which appeared in HZDS activities in that period 
were due to peoples' failures but also discrepancies in the 
system. Meciar said that the HZDS had approved a positive 
manifesto as a basis for a future government programme, and 
elected leading officials who would implement it. 
  The HZDS conference approved new statutes whose wording 
brings the movement's activity closer to that of a political 
party. 

</TEXT>

