<F P=101> Albania </F>
<H3> <TI>   Denmark's Foreign Minister Petersen Visits </TI></H3>
<H4>   Arbnori Briefs Petersen, Delegation </H4>
<F P=102> AU2903095594 Tirana ATA in English 0824 GMT 29 Mar 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU2903095594 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana ATA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tirana, March 29 (ATA) -- During the meeting with 
the Danish foreign minister, Petersen, the speaker of the 
parliament, Pjeter Arbnori, said that like in the past, during 
the years under the communist dictatorship as well, the 
Albanians have always had confidence in the aid of the 
democratic Europe. 
  Mr. Arbnori told the Danish delegation about the composition 
and work of the new pluralistic parliament for the realisation 
of the reform both in the legislative and economic fields. We 
are convinced that we may have mistakes during the economic 
reform we are carrying out but some of them are artificially 
created by the opposition, Mr. Arbnori said. He illustrated his 
statement with the hindrances that the parliamentary commission 
charged with the preparation of the draft of the constitution 
ins encountering. Through these hindrances, the opposition aims 
at bringing Albania back where it was, in a neocommunist 
dictatorship, as it is happening somewhere in Eastern Europe, 
Mr. Arbnori said. 
  Mr. Petersen asked further information about the law on the 
distribution of the land in the countryside, the efforts for the 
new constitution, the resources of Albania and the system of 
taxes applied in this country. 
  Mr. Petersen said that in the context of a three year plan 
for the Eastern and Central European countries, Denmark has 
accorded Albania a considerable financial aid. 

</TEXT>

