<H3> <TI>   Walesa Wants New Candidate </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD3003113094 Warsaw PAP in English 1051 GMT 30 Mar 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> LD3003113094 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw PAP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Warsaw, March 30 -- President Lech Walesa meeting 
with editorial staff of the "SLOWO-DZIENNIK KATOLICKI" daily on 
Wednesday said that he has "no deal" with Prime Minister 
Waldemar Pawlak concerning Dariusz Rosati's candidacy for the 
post of deputy prime minister and finance minister which the 
president rejected on Friday. 
  Walesa, asked whether there is a chance of a compromise in 
the Rosati affair, replied, "Do they want me to desert?" He 
added that it is necessary to find a new candidate for that post 
as quickly as possible. 
  The president referring to the 1994 budget bill, passed by 
the Senate and the Sejm and waiting for the signature of the 
president, said that "for today" he would not sign the budget. 
In his opinion "the nation has been once again cheated, it was 
to be better." He added that he is in despair "from the economic 
point of view" as he knows that apart from minor shifts, nothing 
much can be changed in the budget. 

</TEXT>

