<H3> <TI>   Pawlak Discusses Cooperation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD3003113494 Warsaw PAP in English 1048 GMT 30 Mar 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> LD3003113494 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw PAP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Warsaw, March 30 -- Visiting Canadian Minister of 
Foreign Affairs Andre Ouellet and Prime Minister Waldemar Pawlak 
discussed economic cooperation between Poland and Canada. 
  Prime Minister Pawlak stressed the need to develop direct 
economic contacts among firms and enterprises of the two 
countries. Pawlak and Ouellet also touched upon the issue of 
tourist exchange. 
  They also agreed that a pilot programme on the exchange of 
Polish and Canadian youth will probably be launched soon. The 
Canadian side wants to intensify the exchange of youth with the 
countries of Eastern and Central Europe. 
  Young people from Canada would come to Poland on the same 
principles as voluntaries [as received] from the U.S. Peace 
Corps. Polish youth would travel to Canada on the same 
principles. 

