<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Slovakia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Cabinet To Take Away Meciar's Bodyguard, Staff </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2903195094 Prague CTK in English 1822 GMT 29 Mar 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU2903195094 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bratislava, March 29 (CTK) -- Ex-Premier Vladimir 
Meciar will be able to use the special personal protection 
provided to him by his cabinet on the last day of its existence 
for only three months. The new Slovak Government today 
abolished the resolution about special protection for the 
ex-premier till the end of the electoral term. 
  "We came to the conclusion that there are no reasons for 
special protection of Deputy Meciar," Slovak Deputy Premier Ivan 
Simko told journalists today. He said that under the law Meciar 
had the right to a personal bodyguard for three months and after 
that he could ask new Premier Jozef Moravcik to confirm the 
permission for his personal protection. 
  The Slovak Government today dismissed Anna Nagyova, Meciar's 
close co-worker, from the post of the head of the premier's 
Secretariat. 
  The cabinet also approved the proposal by Vice Premier 
Brigita Schmognerova for the dismissal of Chairman of the Slovak 
Statistics Office Rudolf Krc. Stefan Condik was proposed as new 
chairman. The proposal of Krc's dismissal and the appointment 
of his successor now has to be approved by the president. 

</TEXT>

