<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Slovakia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Second Wave of Privatization To Use Coupons </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2903195194 Prague CTK in English 1815 GMT 29 Mar 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU2903195194 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bratislava, March 29 (CTK) -- Slovak Privatization 
Minister Milan Janicina today said that coupon privatization 
will be the chief method used in the second wave of 
privatization in Slovakia. Slovakia needs a speedy reform of 
the half-communist economic system, while having little capital 
and also little time, Janicina told CTK. 
  He did not dismiss other privatization methods, including 
direct sales, but said that in no case would they be used to the 
same extent as by the Meciar government. 
  "A government coalition deputy cannot be allowed to carry 
out 
a survey and then pass the property into his party colleague's 
hands," said Janicina. He sees direct sales linked mainly with 
foreign investments. 
  Janicina also believes that lucrative enterprises, such as 
Transgas or arms manufacturers, will be included in the second 
wave of voucher privatization. Although nearly 60 percent of 
Slovak enterprises are on the verge of bankruptcy and the real 
value of their property is deep below its nominal appraisal, 
Janicina sees no problem in selecting enterprises for coupon 
privatization. 
  Property worth 100 billion Slovak crowns will be set aside 
for coupon privatization. The government will seek to open the 
preliminary round before the autumn parliamentary elections. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

