<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Slovakia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Coupons Due Out in August </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU3003130494 Prague CTK in English 1050 GMT 30 Mar 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU3003130494 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Trencin, West Slovakia, March 30 (CTK) -- The 
government of Jozef Moravcik and the parties that support it 
plan to launch the second wave of coupon privatization at the 
end of August, Peter Weiss, chairman of the Democratic Left 
Party (SDL), told CTK today. 
  Weiss stated the SDL, a member of the new five party 
coalition government, had always supported a second wave of 
coupon privatization. "It is not just the only chance for people 
who otherwise wouldn't have enough money to take part in the 
privatization process, but it's also a form of investment in the 
future," Weiss said at the Trencin-Fashion City Trade Fair. 
  Weiss said he believed privatization should be a continuous 
process and thus it would be wrong to ask the government to 
shelve the process for six months. 
  Chairman of Parliament Ivan Gasparovic told CTK that he 
doubted the government would manage to prepare the second wave 
in time for the elections, scheduled for September 30 and 
October 1. Property worth 100 billion Slovak crowns ($3.1 
billion) is to be privatized in the second wave. 

</TEXT>

