<F P=100> ALBANIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Rights Group Protests Border Incidents </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2903195294 Tirana TVSH Television Network in Albanian 1800 
GMT 29 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2903195294 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana TVSH Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Albanian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Statement by the Albanian Helsinki Committee] </F>
  [Text] The 21-year-old Fredi Muca has been added to the 
number of Albanians killed on the border. During 1993 and 1994 
the number of Albanians killed along the border with the 
Republic of the Former Yugoslavia amounts to 14 and eight have 
been injured; along the border with The Former Yugoslav Republic 
of Macedonia [FYROM] one has been killed and three injured; and 
along the border the Republic of Greece we note the latest case, 
dated 22 March 1994, which resulted in one person killed. 
  Albanian official sources report that in the Greek village 
of 
Kostinec, 3 km into Greek territory, 21-year-old Fredi Abaz 
Muca, a resident of Bubullime village in Lushnje, was shot by an 
automatic rifle pointed at his chest. 
  The Albanian Helsinki Committee asks the Greek authorities 
to 
take the necessary measures to investigate the incident that 
occurred and eventually convict in a court of law the person who 
caused the crime, on the basis of Greek laws currently in effect. 
  The committee simultaneously requests that such cases be 
stopped and not repeated as they flagrantly violate human rights 
and create tension in the friendly relations that exist between 
the Greek and Albanian Republics. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

