<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Assembly Continues Session, Makes Decisions </TI></H3>
<H4>   Accord With Croatia Endorsed </H4>
<F P=102> LD2903210794 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 2000 GMT 29 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2903210794 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] The Bosnia-Herzegovina Assembly was in session 
in Sarajevo today. [passage omitted] 
  The assembly endorsed an agreement on future military and 
economic cooperation between the federation of 
Bosnia-Herzegovina and the Republic of Croatia, with 83 votes 
for. Continuing, the assembly passed a law on the adoption of 
the draft constitution of the federation of Bosnia-Herzegovina 
and a decision on the adoption of the draft constitution of the 
republic of Bosnia-Herzegovina. A decision on the future work 
of the Assembly of Bosnia-Herzegovina and municipal assemblies 
was also adopted. The assembly is to resume its session at 1000 
tomorrow. 

</TEXT>

