<H3> <TI>   Assembly Continues Session, Makes Decisions </TI></H3>
<H4>   Statement on Negotiation Policy </H4>
<F P=102> AU3003133994 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1203 GMT 30 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU3003133994 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Statement read by the Assembly Secretary General Avdo </F>
Campara and adopted at the session of the Assembly of the 
Republic of Bosnia-Herzegovina in Sarajevo on 30 March -- live] 
  [Text] On the basis of Article 207, Paragraph 2 of the 
Constitution of the Republic of Bosnia-Herzegovina, its text 
amended, the Assembly of the Republic of Bosnia-Herzegovina 
adopts the following statement at the joint Assembly session 
held in Sarajevo on 30 March 1994: 
  Proceeding from the (?outline) of [word indistinct] 
ratification of the Washington agreement, adopted at the session 
of the Assembly of the Republic of Bosnia-Herzegovina held on 27 
March 1994, the Assembly of the Republic of Bosnia-Herzegovina 
demands of the state delegation of the Republic of 
Bosnia-Herzegovina -- in the continuation of the peace 
negotiations on Bosnia-Herzegovina -- to also proceed from the 
Constitutional Law on the Amendments to the Constitution of the 
Republic of Bosnia-Herzegovina, which is a basis for 
establishing a new internal setup of the Republic of 
Bosnia-Herzegovina on the federal bases on the entire territory 
of the Republic of Bosnia-Herzegovina within its internationally 
recognized borders. 
  This statement will be published in the Official Gazetteer 
of 
the Republic of Bosnia-Herzegovina, the same as the statement 
that was read by Mr. Mariofil Ljubic. Thank you. 

</TEXT>

