<H3> <TI>   Karadzic Meets With Russian Delegation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2903165894 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1628 GMT 29 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2903165894 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Sarajevo, 29 Mar (TANJUG) -- President of the Srpska 
republic Radovan Karadzic received a delegation of the Russian 
parliament led by Sergey Baburin in Pale today. Following the 
meeting, Karadzic stated that the Russian parliamentarians' 
visit was important for many reasons. He recalled that Russia 
was involved in the adoption of all resolutions on the Bosnian 
crisis and that Russian soldiers are present in this area. Asked 
whether they discussed the possibility of dispatching fresh 
Russian troops to Bosnia, president Karadzic said the Serb side 
is making steps in that direction, in order to act as a 
counterbalance to soldiers from other countries. The Russian 
parliamentarians visited members of the Russian UN Protection 
Force battalion deployed in Grbavica. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

