<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Islamic Leader Meets With HVO, Muslim Leaders </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2903194594 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1700 GMT 29 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2903194594 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Today Mustafa Efendija Ceric, reis ul ulema of the 
Islamic community of the Republic of Bosnia-Herzegovina, 
received Lieutenant General Ante Roso, commander of the Croatian 
Defense Council [HVO] Headquarters. The reception was also 
attended by Army General Rasim Delic, supreme commander of the 
Chief of Staff of the Bosnia-Herzegovina Armed Forces, and Naib 
Ul Reus Ismet Efendija Spahic. 
  During the long conversation, Reis Ul Ulema Mustafa Efendija 
Ceric supported all the efforts aimed at a military and 
political agreement between the Bosniak and Croatian peoples, 
and stressed that these two peoples are not two sides as they 
have only one homeland, Bosnia-Herzegovina. Their common fate 
is to fight a war for peace and to fight in peace for the 
defense of their own dignity. He stressed that the 1,000-year 
fate of Bosnia was its multicultural character, and that this 
feature was the only basis for the world and its existence. The 
reis ul ulema confirmed that the Islamic community would do all 
it could to help heal the wounds inflicted by the aggression 
upon Bosnia-Herzegovina, which has caused grievous losses to the 
Bosniak people. 
  Expressing his personal conviction as a believer that the 
Islamic community in Bosnia-Herzegovina and its leaders would 
offer help in the healing of the wounds caused by the war, 
Lieutenant General Ante Roso particularly stressed that he had 
come to Sarajevo because he was convinced that everything should 
be done to achieve this end. Saying that the establishment of a 
firm and lasting peace is a difficult task that is beyond the 
powers of any one man, Roso stressed his conviction that this 
could be done through joint efforts. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-9819 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "dreeu061_i_94009" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-EEU-94-061 </AU>
Document Type:Daily Report 
<DATE1>  30 Mar 1994 </DATE1>

