<F P=100> SLOVAKIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Soldiers Fear Army's `Left-Wing Profile' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2903194994 Bratislava REPUBLIKA in Slovak 25 Mar 94 p 3 </F>
<F P=103> AU2903194994 </F>
<F P=104>  Bratislava REPUBLIKA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Slovak </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Article by "rb": "The Army's Wretchedness and Glory; </F>
Association of Slovak Soldiers With the Left at the Ministry of 
Defense"] 
  [Text] Bratislava--The appointment of a civilian as 
minister of defense means the realization by the Ministry of 
Defense of the Slovak Republic of the management model advocated 
by the Association of Slovak Soldiers [ASV] since its founding, 
ASV Chairman Lieutenant Colonel Milan Stegena said yesterday. 
Although this appointment ensures civilian control over the 
Army, this control remains insufficient, according to the ASV. 
It therefore proposes the adoption of a law on the control of 
the Army by the National Council of the Slovak Republic. The 
ASV regards as equally important the establishment of a defense 
committee in the parliament. 
  In view of the political affiliation of Defense Minister 
Pavol Kanis, the ASV chairman expressed fear of a possible 
perpetuation of the left-wing profile of the Army of the Slovak 
Republic. "Left-wing forces are forming groups [grupuju sa] at 
the Ministry of Defense. I would cite the example of Professor 
Bartak," he said. Referring to the unsatisfactory model of 
management relations within the department of the Ministry of 
Defense of the Slovak Republic, he said that the 
military-political and executive components of the Army have not 
been consistently separated to this day. There are frequent 
clashes of power between the Ministry of Defense [in Bratislava] 
and the Command of the Army of the Slovak Republic [in Trencin]. 
The ASV does not want to subject the new leadership of the 
Ministry of Defense of the Slovak Republic to criticism during 
its first 100 days in office. This period will show whether 
visible positive changes will occur within the department. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-9833 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "dreeu061_d_94005" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-EEU-94-061 </AU>
