<H3> <TI>   Half of 1994 Deficit Target Exhausted </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2903194894 Bratislava SME in Slovak 26 Mar 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> AU2903194894 </F>
<F P=104>  Bratislava SME </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Slovak </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Interview with Finance Minister Rudolf Filkus by "is" in </F>
the "Only Question" column; place and date not given: "Budget 
Deficit for First Three Months Stands at 7.5 Billion"] 
  [Text] [SME] Late last year, the National Council of the 
Slovak Republic approved a law on the 1994 state budget, which 
foresees a budget deficit of 14 billion Slovak korunas [Sk]. 
What is the size of the deficit today? 
  [Filkus] As of today, the deficit stands at Sk7.5 billion. 
This demonstrates that the assumption of a deficit at the level 
of Sk14 billion by the end of the year, which was viewed [by the 
previous government] as a realistic macroeconomic indicator, was 
not a realistic macroeconomic assumption. 

</TEXT>

