<F P=101> Albania </F>
<H3> <TI>   Bulgarian Foreign Minister Visits </TI></H3>
<H4>   Meets With Serreqi </H4>
<F P=102> AU2903073594 Sofia BTA in English 1926 GMT 28 Mar 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU2903073594 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia BTA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tirana, March 28 (BTA) -- The formal visit to 
Albania by Bulgarian Foreign Minister Stanislav Daskalov will 
give an impetus to bilateral relations. This observation was 
made at the talks between Daskalov and his Albanian counterpart 
Alfred Serreqi. Daskalov was also received by parliament leader 
Petar Arbnori and Prime Minister Aleksander Meksi. He held 
talks with the leader of the foreign policy committee of the 
Albanian Parliament. 
  No disputes exist between Bulgaria and Albania. The two 
countries value their poltical dialogue and wish to complete 
building the legal basis of their relations which would further 
promote trade and economic cooperation. Bulgaria and Albania 
intend to take part in building an East-West transport corridor 
between the Adriatic and the Black Sea. 
  The sides agreed the promotion of bilateral relations has a 
positive impact on strengthening trust in the Balkans. Bulgaria 
and Albania are interested in a political settlement to the 
crisis in Bosnia and the whole of former Yugoslavia. They 
support the international effort to restore peace and stability 
in the Balkans. 

</TEXT>

