<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Election of New Federation President Postponed </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD3003084494 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in Serbo-Croatian 
0800 GMT 30 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD3003084494 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb Radio Croatia Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] The constituent assembly of the 
Bosnia-Herzegovina Federation is scheduled to start in Sarajevo 
at 1000 today. Zdenko Vranjes reports from Sarajevo. 
  [Vranjes] According to last night's agreements between Croat 
and Muslim representatives, the constituent assembly should 
today simply proclaim the federal constitution, but not elect 
the president and vice president of the Federation for a 
transitional period. 
  According to the leadership of the Croatian representatives, 
the election of the president and vice president of the 
Federation has been postponed for one month at most, because the 
Bosniak Muslim side has not agreed to the proposal put forward 
by Croatian representatives, to the effect that the president of 
the Bosnia-Herzegovina Federation be a Croatian during the 
transitional period. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

