<F P=100> POLAND </F>
<H3> <TI>   Pawlak To Apply for EU Membership in Brussels </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2903140494 Paris AFP in English 1335 GMT 29 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU2903140494 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Warsaw, March 29 (AFP)--The Polish government 
decided Tuesday to make a formal application for EU membership, 
and will propose a negotiation schedule to that end, Polish 
Foreign Minister Andrzej Olechowski told reporters. 
  Olechowski said that Prime Minister Waldemar Pawlak would go 
to Brussels to make the application as soon as the lower house 
of Poland's parliament approves the measure, sometime after 
April 7. 
  Warsaw wants detailed negotiations with the European Union 
to 
begin in 1996 or 1997, finishing before 2000, when Poland could 
become an EU member with a special transitional status. 
  Poland has already signed a "Europe agreement" in 
preparation 
for eventual EU membership. 

</TEXT>

