<F P=100> Haiti </F>
<H3> <TI>   Police Arrest Reported Cali Cartel Drug Networkers </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL2502222094 Port-au-Prince Radio Metropole in French 1700 
GMT 25 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL2502222094 </F>
<F P=104>  Port-au-Prince Radio Metropole </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A drug-trafficking network led by a Colombian man 
was broken over the past few days. According to the head of the 
Information and Joint Coordination Center [CICC], Colonel 
Antoine Atouriste, the head of the drug network, Juan Alberto 
Ramirez (Azurio), reportedly linked to the Cali cartel, was 
arrested on 11 February at his home in (Pegguy-Ville). Five kg 
of cocaine, weapons, ammunition, and $100,000 were seized in 
Ramirez (Azurio)'s home. 
  Two other men from Colombia, two from The Bahamas, and one 
from the Dominican Republic, linked to this network, which is 
considered the most active in recent months in Haiti, were also 
apprehended in the north of the country and in Port-au-Prince, 
according to the head of the CICC. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

