<F P=100> CARIBBEAN </F>
<F P=101> Cuba </F>
<H3> <TI>   Fidel Castro Receives Cypriot Delegation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL2602190694 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 1800 
GMT 26 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL2602190694 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Commander in Chief Fidel Castro has met with 
representatives of the Cypriot Chamber of Commerce headed by its 
president, Alexis Galanos, who is also president of the Cypriot 
Congress' Cyprus-Cuba Friendship Group. 
  The Cypriot delegation that is visiting our country at the 
invitation of the National Assembly of the People's Government 
[ANPP] held a lengthy meeting with the commander in chief, 
exchanging opinions and information on various international 
issues as well as on the respective situations in Cuba and 
Cyprus. 
  Galanos took advantage of this opportunity to say that to 
the 
extent that his country has always enjoyed the firm support of 
Cuba during the most difficult times, the people of Cyprus now 
wish to express their solidarity with the Cuban struggle to 
defend its revolution, through their presence in the country. 
  In addition to the Cypriot deputies, (Georgios 
Paraguiotides), Cypriot consul to Cuba, and ANPP President 
Ricardo Alarcon de Quesada were also present. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>
